HEADWORD: Preocular
<hw>Pre*oc"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Placed just in front of the eyes, as the antenn⟦ae⟧ of certain
insects.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One of the scales just in
front of the eye of a reptile or fish.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

